The '''A388''' is an [[A roads in Great Britain|A road]] in south west [[England]] which runs south from [[Landcross, Devon|Landcross]] south of [[Bideford]] in [[Devon]] through [[Holsworthy, Devon|Holsworthy]], [[Launceston, Cornwall|Launceston]], [[Callington, Cornwall|Callington]] to [[Saltash]] in [[Cornwall]]. 

The A388 begins at a junction with the [[A386 road (England)|A386]] and in Holsworthy has junctions with the A3072. In Launceston it has junctions with the [[A30 road|A30]] and near [[Lawhitton]] a junction with the A384. In Callington it has junctions with the [[A390 road|A390]] and ends at Saltash when it meets the [[A38 road|A38]].<ref>''Reader's Digest New Book of the Road''. London: Reader's Digest Association, 1980</ref>

