The '''Exploration Mission-3''', or '''EM-3''', is a planned 2024 mission of the [[Space Launch System]] and second crewed mission of [[NASA]]'s [[Orion (spacecraft)|Orion]] spacecraft.<ref name="planetary-20180906" /> The intended goal of the mission is to deliver the '''ESPRIT''' and '''U.S. Utilization''' modules to the [[Lunar Orbital Platform-Gateway]] (LOP-G).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sloss|first1=Philip|title=NASA evaluates EM-2 launch options for Deep Space Gateway PPE|url=https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2017/12/nasa-evaluates-em-2-launch-of-space-gateways-ppe/|accessdate=2 March 2018}}</ref>
==Mission objectives== The EM-3 mission plan is to send four astronauts in the second manned [[Orion (spacecraft)|Orion]] capsule into a near-rectilinear halo orbit around the Moon for a maximum of 26 days. It will also deliver two more elements of the future [[Lunar Orbital Platform-Gateway]] (LOP-G), a small [[space station]], to lunar orbit. The LOP-G components will be ESPRIT and the U.S. Utilization Module.<ref name=nsf-20180911>{{cite web |title=NASA updates Lunar Gateway plans |date=September 11, 2017 |first=Philip |last=Sloss |url=https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/09/nasa-lunar-gateway-plans/ |website=NASASpaceFlight.com |access-date=2017-09-15}}</ref> Exploration Missions 3 through 8 would complete the assembly of the Lunar Gateway.<ref name="Insider20170401">{{cite news |last=Godwin |first=Curt |url=http://www.spaceflightinsider.com/organizations/nasa/nasa-human-spaceflight-plans-focus-announcement-deep-space-gateway/ |title=NASA's human spaceflight plans come into focus with announcement of Deep Space Gateway |newspaper=Spaceflight Insider |date=April 1, 2017 |accessdate=2017-04-02 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Chris Gebhardt |url=http://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2015/09/sls-manifest-phobos-mars-2039/ |title=SLS manifest options aim for Phobos prior to 2039 Mars landing |website=NASASpaceFlight.com |date=2015-09-22 |accessdate=2017-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasa.gov/press/2015/march/nasa-announces-next-steps-on-journey-to-mars-progress-on-asteroid-initiative |title=NASA Announces Progress on Asteroid Initiative &#124; NASA |website=Nasa.gov |date= |accessdate=2017-03-30}}</ref>
